Tonight at least 4,000 families of staff working at the country's national airline, Kenya airways will be waiting with bated breath as to whether the struggling airline will receive a 28 billion&nbsp;shillings&rsquo; bailout package or not. Failure to secure it will be catastrophic, this could see the loss making airline stall its operations completely which could resort in massive job losses.&nbsp;This comes hot on the heels of the just released results which saw the airline report a 36.5 billion shillings&rsquo; loss&nbsp;the highest ever reported by a company in Kenya&rsquo;s corporate history. But what happened?